cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.CC

This paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for coloring graphs, which are topics that are commonly found in the arXiv sub-categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Graph Theory (cs.GT), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). However, since the paper focuses on a specific class of graphs (those without odd holes, antiholes, and prisms), it is more likely to be classified under cs.DM or cs.GT.
